Package: heuristica
Title: Heuristics including Take The Best and unit-weight linear
Version: 1.0.0.0000
Authors@R: person("Jean", "imal", email = "jeanimal@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements various heuristics like Take The Best and
    unit-weight linear, called Dawes' model here, in a format that
    makes it easy to use with other R fit models.  In particular,
    they implement coef and predict.  Includes helper functions.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
Imports:
    Hmisc
URL: https://github.com/jeanimal/heuristica
Suggests:
    devtools,
    ggplot2,
    knitr,
    plyr,
    reshape,
    reshape2,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
